text:
Arthur Kill: Shown is the shore of Holland Hook, Staten Island, and Ivoryport--the Procter and Gamble ivory soap works. On the extreme left is the ferry landing, at the foot of Richmond Terrace, and the ferryboat "Irvington." View 3 shows also the cinder, dock freight yard of the Baltimore and Ohio Railroad.

June 14, 1935
Views 1, 2, 3

P. L. Sperr
title: Arthur Kill - Holland Hook - Staten Island [Richmond - Ivoryport - Procter and Gamble Ivory soap works.]
